The National Directorate of Employment (NDE) has trained 350 youths drawn from the 17 Local Government Areas on basic business skills in Plateau State. According to the Director General (DG) of NDE, Dr. Nasir Muhammad Ladan Argungu, represented by the State Coordinator, Mallam Ibrahim Abdullazeez Hardo, the training which is in collaboration with the Minister of Women Affairs and Social Development, Pauline Talen, is meant to engage unemployed youths in businesses in the state and the country in general.  The National Directorate of Employment (NDE) has trained 350 youths drawn from the 17 Local Government Areas on basic business skills in Plateau State. According to the Director General (DG) of NDE, Dr. Nasir Muhammad Ladan Argungu, represented by the State Coordinator, Mallam Ibrahim Abdullazeez Hardo, the training which is in collaboration with the Minister of Women Affairs and Social Development, Pauline Talen, is meant to engage unemployed youths in businesses in the state and the country in general. 